slots.description: All application markup should be placed within the default slot.

members.name: theme
members.description: Optionally specifies light/dark mode. This is only needed if the application can change the theme separate from OS settings.

members.name: sx
members.description: Supports adding inline styles as an object

slots.description: The button's label, which may contain markup such as icons, is placed in the default slot.

members.name: tag
members.description: Specifies whether the button is a true button element or "link button."

members.name: type
members.description: The `type` attribute of the button: button, submit, or reset. Defaults to "button."

members.name: fill
members.description: The visual fill of the button: solid, outline, or ghost. Defaults to "solid."

members.name: color
members.description: The color of the button: primary, secondary, or danger. Defaults to "primary."

members.name: variant
members.description: Specifies a variant of the buttons, such as square for buttons with only an icon and call-to-action button.

members.name: value
members.description: The `value` attribute of the button, which is passed as part of formData for the the pressed submit button.

members.name: href
members.description: The `href` attribute of a link button.

members.name: rel
members.description: The `rel` attribute of a link button.

members.name: target
members.description: The `target` attribute of a link button.

members.name: download
members.description:
The `download` attribute of a link button; when present tells the browser to download the specified href URI instead
of viewing or navigating to it.

members.name: width
members.description: Specifies the (min-)width of the button (in CSS units) when different from the default size.

members.name: height
members.description: Specifies the (min-)height of the button (in CSS units) when different from the default size.

members.name: pressed
members.description: Specifies if the button is pressed and results in `aria-pressed="true"` being placed on the button when true. Only valid on actual `button` elements.

members.name: expanded
members.description:
Specifies if a controlled UI widget is expanded and results in `aria-pressed="true"` being placed on the button when true.
This property is usually used for progressive disclosure patterns such as accordions, menus, expand/collapse, etc., where
focus remains on the control after the user action.

members.name: controls
members.description:
Specifies the DOM element that the button controls and results in the `aria-controls` attribute
rendered on the button with the specified value.

members.name: targetProp
members.description: The property on the target element being toggled by the button/control.

members.name: accessibilityText
members.description:
Specifies an accessible label for the button/link as an `aria-label` when the button does not contain label text
or a sufficiently unique label. This text overrides the default label and is not additive to it.

members.name: disabled
members.description: Marks the rendered button/link in a disabled state when specified.

members.name: sx
members.description: Supports adding inline styles as an object

events.name: buttonClick
events.description: A custom event emitted when the click event occurs for either a rendered button or anchor/link.

events.name: componentLoad
events.description: A custom event emitted when the component has completed loading and its internal lifecycles.

members.description: Specifies the grid display. Defaults to "grid".

members.name: gridTemplateAreas
members.description: Defines the grid via named grid areas, which provides a visualization of the structure of the grid.

members.name: gridTemplateColumns
members.description: Specifies the track sizing functions (and optionally line names) of the grid columns as a space-separated track list

members.name: gridTemplateRows
members.description: Specifies the track sizing functions (and optionally line names) of the grid rows as a space-separated track list

members.name: gridAutoFlow
members.description: Specifies how auto-placed items get flowed into the grid.

members.name: gridAutoColumns
members.description: Specifies the size of implicitly-created columns using the auto-placement algorithm.

members.name: gridAutoRows
members.description: Specifies the size of implicitly-created rows using the auto-placement algorithm.

members.name: alignItems
members.description: Aligns grid items in the vertical/column axis, perpendicular to the inline axis.

members.name: justifyItems
members.description: Justifies grid content horizontally, along the inline/row axis.

members.name: alignContent
members.description: Aligns grid content vertically when total grid size is smaller than container.

members.name: justifyContent
members.description: Justifies grid content horizontally when total grid size is smaller than container.

members.name: gap
members.description: Specifies the spacing between grid items in the form of a single value or space-separated row-gap and column-gap values in CSS units

members.name: breakpoint
members.description: The size (in CSS units; preferably relative units such as `rem`) below which the grid items linearize.

members.name: display
members.description: Specifies the host's display when visible. The default is `inline`, which is the default display of a custom element.

members.name: hide
members.description: When set to true, the host is hidden. Allows for toggling via property binding rather than media query.

members.name: visuallyHide
members.description: When set to true, the host is visually hidden in an accessible manner. Allows for toggling via property binding rather than media query.

members.name: hideAt
members.description: Specifies a valid CSS media query (preferably using relative units), when met will hide the wrapped content using display: none. E.g., `max-width: 64em`

members.name: visuallyHideAt
members.description: Specifies a valid CSS media query (preferably using relative units), when met will visually hide the wrapped content in a way that is it still accessible as a label. E.g., `max-width: 64em`
